      "side": 1,
      "message": "There are multiple upstream configurations which are probing on interfaces which (could be) exposed by EM.\n\nhttps://github.com/openbmc/entity-manager/blob/d40558216ad85e99f3c37614fc96e088241a4f72/configurations/meta/bletchley/bletchley_frontpanel.json#L90\n\nis probing on `xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Decorator.Asset`\n\nhttps://github.com/openbmc/entity-manager/blob/d40558216ad85e99f3c37614fc96e088241a4f72/configurations/ibm/sbp1_rssd.json#L381\n\nis probing on `xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item`\n\nhttps://github.com/openbmc/entity-manager/blob/d40558216ad85e99f3c37614fc96e088241a4f72/configurations/ibm/tacoma_rack_controller.json#L20\n\nis probing on `xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Decorator.Asset`\n\nAs a consequence, someone wanting to stop EM from probing it\u0027s own interfaces must check that in those instances the interface is not coming from EM. Otherwise risk of breaking stuff.",
